# Delegated Inference

Delegate model loading and completion requests to a remote peer via Hyperswarm, while keeping the same SDK API surface.

## Schema

Defined in `packages/sdk/schemas/delegate.ts`. The `delegate` field (optional) includes `topic` (Hyperswarm topic hex), `providerPublicKey` (hex), optional `timeout`, `fallbackToLocal` (default false), and `forceNewConnection` (default false). It's included in every `loadModel` request variant via `loadModelCommonFields` in `schemas/load-model.ts`.

## Architecture

### Shared Hyperswarm — `server/bare/hyperswarm.ts`

Module-scoped singleton created via `getSwarm()`. Uses deterministic seed from `QVAC_HYPERSWARM_SEED` env var (or random), configurable firewall function (allow/deny by public key), relay support via SDK config's `swarmRelays`. Also exports `registerProviderTopic()`, `unregisterProviderTopic()`, `hasActiveProviders()`, `destroySwarm()`.

### Delegate RPC Client — `server/bare/delegate-rpc-client.ts`

Manages Hyperswarm peer connections and `bare-rpc` instances. `getRPC(topic, publicKey, options)` returns an RPC instance connected to the target peer. Caches RPC/connection by public key, supports `forceNewConnection`. `cleanupStaleConnection(publicKey)` removes dead connections.

### Delegate Transport — `server/rpc/delegate-transport.ts`

`send(request, rpc, options)` for single request/response, `stream(request, rpc, options)` for streaming. Both serialize to JSON and support profiling when enabled.

### Load Model Delegated — `server/rpc/handlers/load-model-delegated.ts`

Gets RPC connection, strips `delegate` field from request (prevents infinite delegation), sends to provider. On success: registers model as delegated (`isDelegated: true`) with topic/publicKey/timeout. On failure with `fallbackToLocal: true`: attempts local `handleLoadModel()`.

### Completion Stream Delegated — `server/rpc/handlers/completion-stream-delegated.ts`

Looks up model in registry, verifies `entry.isDelegated`, gets RPC connection, streams completion, yields each chunk.

### Model Registry — `server/bare/registry/model-registry.ts`

`ModelEntry` supports both local and delegated models. `registerModel()` accepts either local options or `{ topic, providerPublicKey, timeout }` for delegation.

